1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:02,210
[Marcus] <i>Another group</i>
<i>really did start the chaos</i>

2
00:00:02,293 --> 00:00:03,837
<i>on the island that night.</i>

3
00:00:03,920 --> 00:00:05,505
<i>Datu Rahman is innocent.</i>

4
00:00:05,588 --> 00:00:07,465
<i>Someone planted the intel we received.</i>

5
00:00:07,549 --> 00:00:10,051
<i>Straight from the mouth</i>
<i>of the high-ranking smuggler</i>

6
00:00:10,135 --> 00:00:11,052
<i>I fought on the island.</i>

7
00:00:11,136 --> 00:00:13,430
<i>Their protector is someone</i>
<i>inside the NLEA.</i>

8
00:00:13,513 --> 00:00:14,973
<i>There's something else</i>
<i>you should know, sir.</i>

9
00:00:15,056 --> 00:00:17,392
<i>I took Datu Rahman out</i>
<i>of the Zylverix Building.</i>

10
00:00:17,475 --> 00:00:18,435
Where is he now?!

11
00:00:18,518 --> 00:00:20,562
[Marcus] <i>The people who kidnapped him</i>
<i>tracked him down.</i>

12
00:00:20,645 --> 00:00:23,398
<i>But his son managed to save him.</i>

13
00:00:23,481 --> 00:00:26,818
You need to help Allan Espina.

14
00:00:26,901 --> 00:00:28,695
[Ahmad] <i>Help Jalil on his mission.</i>

15
00:00:28,778 --> 00:00:30,655
[Usman] <i>Why don't we</i>
<i>just tell him the truth?</i>

16
00:00:30,739 --> 00:00:31,656
<i>You share the same goal anyway.</i>

17
00:00:31,740 --> 00:00:33,575
[Jalil] I can't tell you all my plans!

18
00:00:33,658 --> 00:00:35,952
You just have to trust me!
We know what we're doing.

19
00:00:36,036 --> 00:00:38,747
[Dionisio] <i>Azuelo has finally</i>
<i>put his trust in Reyes.</i>

20
00:00:38,830 --> 00:00:40,415
[Manuel] <i>Just leave him be.</i>

21
00:00:40,498 --> 00:00:43,626
[in English] I have something
in mind for that man.

22
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:46,629
[Ahmad] <i>If what you're saying</i>
<i>is true, prove it.</i>

23
00:00:46,713 --> 00:00:48,840
<i>I'll give you a chance.</i>

24
00:00:48,923 --> 00:00:50,550
<i>Surrender yourself to me.</i>

25
00:00:50,633 --> 00:00:52,761
I'll wait for you, brother.

26
00:00:52,844 --> 00:00:55,430
All of this is happening

27
00:00:55,513 --> 00:00:57,724
because you lost Datu Rahman.

28
00:00:57,807 --> 00:01:00,852
<i>And if they manage to get him,</i>

29
00:01:00,935 --> 00:01:02,062
<i>we're done!</i>

30
00:01:02,145 --> 00:01:04,397
[Azuelo] <i>Our image is ruined</i>
<i>in the public's eyes.</i>

31
00:01:04,481 --> 00:01:07,650
<i>We need to purge the entire agency.</i>

32
00:01:07,734 --> 00:01:10,487
I think we need to show people

33
00:01:10,570 --> 00:01:12,655
that we can hold people accountable,

34
00:01:12,739 --> 00:01:14,449
whether they're our colleagues or not.

35
00:01:14,532 --> 00:01:16,743
[Villanueva] <i>You speak to the press.</i>

36
00:01:17,952 --> 00:01:20,747
[Marcus] <i>You are willing to do anything</i>
<i>to save your father.</i>

37
00:01:20,830 --> 00:01:25,043
<i>But the people behind this conspiracy</i>
<i>will not let you both live.</i>

38
00:01:25,126 --> 00:01:27,796
<i>So you have to work with me.</i>

39
00:01:28,546 --> 00:01:29,756
[man] <i>What do you need here?</i>

40
00:01:29,839 --> 00:01:31,925
[Malik] <i>You're probably here</i>
<i>to cause trouble again, aren't you?</i>

41
00:01:32,008 --> 00:01:35,178
[Espina] <i>I'm here to pick up Datu Rahman.</i>

42
00:01:35,261 --> 00:01:36,846
[suspenseful music playing]

43
00:01:39,432 --> 00:01:46,356
[mysterious theme music playing]

44
00:01:54,614 --> 00:01:55,949
[pensive music playing]

45
00:01:56,032 --> 00:01:58,076
What? Hold on.

46
00:01:58,159 --> 00:01:59,661
Datu Rahman isn't here.

47
00:01:59,744 --> 00:02:02,831
[Idah] And why are you looking for him?

48
00:02:02,914 --> 00:02:05,083
Datu Rahman is not a criminal.

49
00:02:05,750 --> 00:02:07,502
He was wrongly accused.

50
00:02:08,086 --> 00:02:10,004
Datu Rahman surrendered himself to me.

51
00:02:10,088 --> 00:02:11,256
- [Ibrahim] What?
- I'll pick him up.

52
00:02:11,339 --> 00:02:12,966
- Hey! what do you mean?
- Sir! Sir!

53
00:02:13,049 --> 00:02:14,551
- What are you talking about?!
- [overlapping dialogue]

54
00:02:14,634 --> 00:02:15,802
- Hey!
- Stop it!

55
00:02:16,636 --> 00:02:18,888
[woman] Sir, this is wrong.

56
00:02:18,972 --> 00:02:20,265
[Malik] You're putting
yourself in trouble.

57
00:02:20,348 --> 00:02:22,392
- [Ibrahim] Datu Rahman isn't here!
- Hold on!

58
00:02:22,475 --> 00:02:23,768
[Malik] Sir, this isn't right.

59
00:02:23,852 --> 00:02:25,186
- He's right!
- Sir, stop it!

60
00:02:25,270 --> 00:02:26,312
Sir.

61
00:02:26,396 --> 00:02:28,231
[overlapping angry chatter]

62
00:02:28,314 --> 00:02:30,191
- He's not here!
- [Malik] Sir, listen to us.

63
00:02:30,275 --> 00:02:33,194
[Ibrahim] This isn't right, sir.
This isn't right.

64
00:02:33,278 --> 00:02:34,904
- [woman] Mr. Omar!
- [Malik] Sir! Sir!

65
00:02:34,988 --> 00:02:35,822
[overlapping chatter]

66
00:02:35,905 --> 00:02:37,031
Hold on, hold on.

67
00:02:38,867 --> 00:02:40,076
Don't worry.

68
00:02:40,618 --> 00:02:42,537
- He's on our side.
- [crowd gasps]

69
00:02:42,620 --> 00:02:44,038
- How did that happen?
- He's a cop!

70
00:02:44,122 --> 00:02:45,331
He's a cop, Mister Omar!

71
00:02:45,415 --> 00:02:47,625
Have you forgotten about what happened?

72
00:02:47,709 --> 00:02:50,086
[tense music playing]

73
00:02:54,757 --> 00:02:56,175
[Ibrahim] Datu Rahman's here!

74
00:02:56,759 --> 00:02:57,969
- He's here.
- Since when is he here?

75
00:02:58,052 --> 00:02:59,929
- It's really him.
- [woman] It's true. He's here.

76
00:03:04,559 --> 00:03:06,144
I will go with him.

77
00:03:06,227 --> 00:03:07,312
- [crowd gasps]
- [woman] Why?

78
00:03:07,395 --> 00:03:09,230
[Datu Rahman] Don't worry.

79
00:03:10,189 --> 00:03:11,858
He will protect me.

80
00:03:14,819 --> 00:03:16,821
[indistinct chattering]

81
00:03:16,905 --> 00:03:18,239
- [Ibrahim] He's a cop.
- [Rashid] We can't be sure.

82
00:03:18,323 --> 00:03:19,741
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

83
00:03:21,492 --> 00:03:23,119
[in Arabic] And peace be upon you.

84
00:03:35,590 --> 00:03:37,133
Mister Omar…

85
00:03:42,305 --> 00:03:43,848
[handcuffs rattling]

86
00:03:43,932 --> 00:03:50,355
[pensive music playing]

87
00:04:19,133 --> 00:04:20,510
Thank you so much

88
00:04:21,594 --> 00:04:23,805
for your concern for my well-being.

89
00:04:27,558 --> 00:04:28,393
[in Tausug] Thank you.

90
00:04:42,740 --> 00:04:49,622
[tense music playing]

91
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:56,838
[music intensifies]

92
00:04:58,298 --> 00:05:00,133
- [music turns somber]
- [Idah] Sir, keep your promise!

93
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,552
He's innocent!

94
00:05:03,970 --> 00:05:05,096
Look after Datu Rahman!

95
00:05:05,179 --> 00:05:06,806
Keep your promise!

96
00:05:07,473 --> 00:05:09,642
- [man] Datu Rahman!
- [woman] Datu Rahman!

97
00:05:09,726 --> 00:05:10,560
[Ibrahim] Mister Omar!

98
00:05:12,103 --> 00:05:13,813
[car blips]

99
00:05:15,189 --> 00:05:17,984
[ethereal music playing]

100
00:05:34,042 --> 00:05:36,002
[Jamilah sobs, sniffles]

101
00:05:36,085 --> 00:05:37,378
Take care, Father.

102
00:05:42,175 --> 00:05:44,510
Please look after my father…

103
00:05:46,054 --> 00:05:46,971
sir.

104
00:05:48,556 --> 00:05:49,390
‪[rooster crowing]

105
00:05:55,354 --> 00:05:56,481
[Omar sobs]

106
00:06:01,110 --> 00:06:02,695
[man] Datu Rahman…

107
00:06:04,906 --> 00:06:06,199
[car door clicks shut]

108
00:06:06,282 --> 00:06:12,038
[ethereal music continues]

109
00:06:42,151 --> 00:06:44,153
[pensive music playing]

110
00:06:44,654 --> 00:06:46,864
Marcus. Let's talk.

111
00:06:50,451 --> 00:06:52,620
Why is Datu Rahman
targeting you in his video?

112
00:06:53,329 --> 00:06:54,914
And where did he get the information

113
00:06:54,997 --> 00:06:56,415
that there is a traitor here in the NLEA?

114
00:06:57,250 --> 00:06:58,459
Why are you asking me that?

115
00:06:58,543 --> 00:06:59,544
[Lara scoffs softly]

116
00:07:00,211 --> 00:07:01,712
Isn't it always coming from you

117
00:07:01,796 --> 00:07:03,256
that there is a traitor here in the NLEA?

118
00:07:05,383 --> 00:07:06,509
Lara, just be straight with me.

119
00:07:06,592 --> 00:07:07,510
What do you really want to know?

120
00:07:07,593 --> 00:07:09,387
Did you talk to Datu Rahman?

121
00:07:14,642 --> 00:07:15,643
Where is this coming from?

122
00:07:16,602 --> 00:07:19,397
Lara, I'm looking for Datu Rahman.

123
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:20,731
That's my job.

124
00:07:21,399 --> 00:07:22,442
[in English] Really?

125
00:07:24,444 --> 00:07:26,446
So when you went on leave
without telling anyone,

126
00:07:26,529 --> 00:07:27,655
where did you really go?

127
00:07:29,824 --> 00:07:31,742
And when Datu Rahman was taken
from Zylverix, where were you then?

128
00:07:31,826 --> 00:07:33,369
[in English] Where were you?

129
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:35,872
Are you accusing me, Lara?

130
00:07:37,373 --> 00:07:38,916
Didn't we already talk about this?

131
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,710
No, I'm not accusing you.

132
00:07:41,461 --> 00:07:42,837
But be honest with me.

133
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:45,047
Don't you trust me?

134
00:07:45,882 --> 00:07:48,134
Or do you suspect me?

135
00:07:48,217 --> 00:07:50,219
Why would I suspect you?

136
00:07:51,554 --> 00:07:53,097
Are you hiding something?

137
00:07:55,224 --> 00:07:56,267
Nothing.

138
00:07:58,102 --> 00:07:59,687
So there's nothing then.

139
00:08:00,980 --> 00:08:03,649
We still have a lot to solve, Lara.

140
00:08:03,733 --> 00:08:05,693
Let's not worry about things we shouldn't.

141
00:08:05,776 --> 00:08:10,323
[pensive music continues]

142
00:08:25,338 --> 00:08:31,093
[somber music playing]

143
00:08:31,177 --> 00:08:32,887
Don't worry, Jamilah.

144
00:08:32,970 --> 00:08:34,847
Your father will be okay too.

145
00:08:37,517 --> 00:08:38,684
[softly] Talk to her.

146
00:08:42,522 --> 00:08:43,606
Jamilah.

147
00:08:45,608 --> 00:08:46,901
He's right.

148
00:08:46,984 --> 00:08:49,904
Your brother Jalil won't let
anything happen to him.

149
00:08:50,988 --> 00:08:52,031
Okay?

150
00:09:06,754 --> 00:09:10,174
[dramatic sting]

151
00:09:29,777 --> 00:09:30,611
Son.

152
00:09:32,321 --> 00:09:33,364
Pa.

153
00:09:35,491 --> 00:09:39,161
I've thought about it, and you're right.

154
00:09:40,705 --> 00:09:42,915
You need to go back to the island.

155
00:09:44,041 --> 00:09:46,836
Check on our fellow villagers.

156
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:49,880
They went through major damage.

157
00:09:51,090 --> 00:09:52,675
They need you.

158
00:09:54,385 --> 00:09:57,138
[Jalil] Yes, Papa. That's a promise.

159
00:09:58,472 --> 00:10:00,474
[Datu Rahman] Also tell them

160
00:10:00,558 --> 00:10:02,893
that I have not forgotten them,

161
00:10:03,769 --> 00:10:06,230
and that I will return
once everything here is settled.

162
00:10:07,481 --> 00:10:09,275
[Jalil] Yes, Papa.

163
00:10:18,576 --> 00:10:20,703
[line ringing]

164
00:10:21,787 --> 00:10:22,830
Sir.

165
00:10:24,123 --> 00:10:26,626
[dramatic sting]

166
00:10:26,709 --> 00:10:27,752
‪[ethereal music playing]

167
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:30,755
‪[dramatic sting]

168
00:10:35,426 --> 00:10:36,260
‪[music concludes]

169
00:10:37,553 --> 00:10:38,721
Agent Reyes.

170
00:10:39,472 --> 00:10:40,389
Sir.

171
00:10:41,140 --> 00:10:45,102
You need to assemble
Task Force Alpha right now.

172
00:10:45,686 --> 00:10:48,939
[in English] I want everybody ready
in five minutes.

173
00:10:49,649 --> 00:10:50,858
Why, sir?

174
00:10:51,442 --> 00:10:52,985
We will be meeting someone

175
00:10:53,069 --> 00:10:56,238
who requires maximum security protection.

176
00:10:56,322 --> 00:10:58,115
- [in English] Go.
- [in English] Copy, sir.

177
00:10:59,367 --> 00:11:04,246
[mysterious music playing]

178
00:11:09,168 --> 00:11:10,711
[door clicks open]

179
00:11:13,339 --> 00:11:14,799
[in English] What's going on?

180
00:11:15,424 --> 00:11:17,051
A VIP is arriving.

181
00:11:17,134 --> 00:11:19,595
Oh, since when did we become VIP escorts?

182
00:11:20,679 --> 00:11:22,348
I don't know the full details yet.

183
00:11:23,474 --> 00:11:26,143
I am only following orders
from Director Azuelo.

184
00:11:27,436 --> 00:11:30,064
Whoever this person is,
their life is in danger.

185
00:11:30,689 --> 00:11:32,775
And we need to protect them.

186
00:11:32,858 --> 00:11:37,113
[mysterious music continues]

187
00:11:51,001 --> 00:11:52,461
- [in English] Hello.
- Hey.

188
00:11:53,462 --> 00:11:54,672
[in English] Hi, General Carillo.

189
00:11:54,755 --> 00:11:57,925
[in English] Hi. Hi. Hello. [chuckles]

190
00:11:58,008 --> 00:11:58,843
[in English] Take your seats.

191
00:11:58,926 --> 00:12:01,262
What can I do for you?

192
00:12:01,345 --> 00:12:03,556
[man] Well, as you know, General Carillo,

193
00:12:03,639 --> 00:12:06,308
next week, the Japanese delegates
will arrive

194
00:12:06,392 --> 00:12:08,519
to discuss the investment deal.

195
00:12:09,603 --> 00:12:12,731
[woman] This is not only important
in terms of uplifting the economy,

196
00:12:12,815 --> 00:12:14,400
it is also historic.

197
00:12:14,483 --> 00:12:15,776
[in English] Yes, and uh…

198
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:22,867
Because of the… [clears throat]
…unrest happening nowadays…

199
00:12:22,950 --> 00:12:24,243
You're right, General.

200
00:12:24,326 --> 00:12:27,913
- We need stricter security for this event.
- [Manuel sighs]

201
00:12:27,997 --> 00:12:30,916
We would like to get you as a consultant.

202
00:12:31,834 --> 00:12:35,337
I am honored to follow the call of duty.

203
00:12:36,005 --> 00:12:37,047
[in English] I assure you.

204
00:12:37,131 --> 00:12:41,218
[in English] All those delegates
will be safe and secure.

205
00:12:41,302 --> 00:12:44,555
[in English] Oh, well,
that's great, General Carillo!

206
00:12:44,638 --> 00:12:46,182
[in English] My pleasure, my pleasure.

207
00:12:46,265 --> 00:12:47,141
- [in English] Thank you, sir.
- [in English] My pleasure.

208
00:12:47,224 --> 00:12:48,601
- [in English] Thank you, General.
- [in English] You're welcome.

209
00:12:48,684 --> 00:12:50,644
[phone ringing]

210
00:12:50,728 --> 00:12:53,814
Uh, excuse me.
Sorry, I need to answer this.

211
00:12:53,898 --> 00:12:55,649
- Okay.
- Keep doing what you're doing.

212
00:12:55,733 --> 00:12:56,984
I'll be back.

213
00:12:57,067 --> 00:12:58,194
- [phone ringing]
- [Manuel clears throat]

214
00:12:58,277 --> 00:13:00,613
[tense music playing]

215
00:13:01,322 --> 00:13:02,364
[Manuel sighs]

216
00:13:02,448 --> 00:13:04,033
- Lara.
- [in English] Dad.

217
00:13:05,367 --> 00:13:07,203
They said a VIP's coming here.

218
00:13:07,786 --> 00:13:09,914
TFA itself is protecting the VIP.

219
00:13:09,997 --> 00:13:11,457
[in English] Something's
happening here, Dad.

220
00:13:12,249 --> 00:13:13,792
And you don't know what it is.

221
00:13:13,876 --> 00:13:17,713
[tense music playing]

222
00:13:17,796 --> 00:13:18,631
[Manuel] <i>Lara.</i>

223
00:13:19,465 --> 00:13:24,637
I placed you in that position
to be my eyes and ears

224
00:13:24,720 --> 00:13:27,515
inside NLEA and SID.

225
00:13:27,598 --> 00:13:29,808
So, if something's going on

226
00:13:29,892 --> 00:13:31,268
that you don't know about,

227
00:13:31,352 --> 00:13:33,812
then you are not doing your job well!

228
00:13:54,416 --> 00:13:58,087
[music intensifies]

229
00:14:10,057 --> 00:14:11,725
Who are we waiting for?

230
00:14:13,018 --> 00:14:14,270
I don't know either.

231
00:14:15,229 --> 00:14:16,355
[Felix scoffs]

232
00:14:17,189 --> 00:14:19,024
This bastard thinks he's so important.

233
00:14:19,108 --> 00:14:23,195
[suspenseful music playing]

234
00:14:43,757 --> 00:14:45,134
[car door clicks shut]

235
00:14:50,431 --> 00:14:55,603
[pensive music playing]

236
00:15:10,034 --> 00:15:11,827
[dramatic music playing]

237
00:15:43,984 --> 00:15:49,823
[dramatic music continues]

238
00:16:11,095 --> 00:16:12,221
Major Espina.

239
00:16:14,264 --> 00:16:15,265
Sir.

240
00:16:16,976 --> 00:16:18,143
He surrendered to me earlier.

241
00:16:20,062 --> 00:16:23,232
He wants to surrender to Ahmad Mustapha.

242
00:16:25,401 --> 00:16:27,319
[in English] Good job, Major Espina!

243
00:16:27,403 --> 00:16:31,865
[mysterious music playing]

244
00:17:11,155 --> 00:17:17,619
[music intensifies]

245
00:18:17,429 --> 00:18:24,269
[tense music playing]

246
00:19:07,062 --> 00:19:09,606
[breathing heavily]

247
00:19:09,690 --> 00:19:11,024
[in English] Felix,
you have to do something.

248
00:19:11,692 --> 00:19:13,819
Mustapha cannot get
his hands on Datu Rahman.

249
00:19:14,611 --> 00:19:15,904
What do you want me to do?

250
00:19:16,947 --> 00:19:19,491
Do you want me to kill
Datu Rahman right here?

251
00:19:21,034 --> 00:19:24,830
[sinister music playing]

252
00:19:39,761 --> 00:19:41,471
How did you manage to do it?

253
00:19:42,723 --> 00:19:44,516
How did you manage to find Datu Rahman?

254
00:19:46,727 --> 00:19:48,979
[Jalil] That's why
I was sent here, wasn't I?

255
00:19:50,439 --> 00:19:53,525
It's because Muslims have trust in me.

256
00:19:53,609 --> 00:19:57,362
Datu Rahman trusted me,
so he came with me.

257
00:19:58,447 --> 00:19:59,907
That's my job.

258
00:20:00,574 --> 00:20:04,661
So I hope you and Task Force Alpha
will also do your job.

259
00:20:04,745 --> 00:20:06,496
Protect Datu Rahman.

260
00:20:07,122 --> 00:20:10,584
At least, until the Presidential
Chief of Staff comes here.

261
00:20:11,585 --> 00:20:13,587
You can do that, can't you?

262
00:20:18,383 --> 00:20:20,177
[pensive music playing]

263
00:20:20,260 --> 00:20:22,179
I know how to do my job.

264
00:20:26,016 --> 00:20:29,394
Reyes, I know that
you hid away Datu Rahman.

265
00:20:30,979 --> 00:20:34,107
I know you also hid him
away from Zylverix.

266
00:20:34,191 --> 00:20:37,611
[dramatic sting]

267
00:20:37,694 --> 00:20:38,612
Thank you…

268
00:20:41,114 --> 00:20:42,366
for what you've done.

269
00:20:48,247 --> 00:20:50,415
- How did you know--
- Don't worry.

270
00:20:51,124 --> 00:20:53,293
Reyes, I understand why you did that.

271
00:20:55,337 --> 00:20:56,922
I won't tell anyone about it.

272
00:20:57,547 --> 00:20:58,924
This secret will stay between us.

273
00:21:01,969 --> 00:21:03,053
Thank you.

274
00:21:03,136 --> 00:21:06,014
[pensive music playing]

275
00:21:26,368 --> 00:21:27,953
[in English] Finally!

276
00:21:28,662 --> 00:21:29,746
[Azuelo] We finally won.

277
00:21:30,998 --> 00:21:31,957
[glass thuds]

278
00:21:35,002 --> 00:21:38,213
Ahmad Mustapha and the media
will be delighted

279
00:21:38,297 --> 00:21:39,506
with what you have done.

280
00:21:39,589 --> 00:21:42,634
You were able to make
Datu Rahman surrender.

281
00:21:42,718 --> 00:21:45,095
That's a big deal, Major Espina.

282
00:21:46,221 --> 00:21:50,142
I'm sorry, sir, but my face
can't be shown to the media.

283
00:21:50,726 --> 00:21:53,103
I still have some ongoing missions.

284
00:21:53,186 --> 00:21:54,813
It might hinder me, sir.

285
00:21:54,896 --> 00:21:56,273
Are you sure?

286
00:21:56,773 --> 00:21:58,233
Don't want to be famous?

287
00:21:58,317 --> 00:22:00,319
Yes, sir. I'm sure.

288
00:22:03,280 --> 00:22:04,281
[in English] Understood.

289
00:22:05,741 --> 00:22:06,783
[in English] Sir.

290
00:22:06,867 --> 00:22:10,245
[pensive music continues]

291
00:22:19,087 --> 00:22:21,465
- [cameras clicking]
- [overlapping chatter]

292
00:22:21,548 --> 00:22:22,716
[reporter 1] Sir! Sir! Sir!

293
00:22:22,799 --> 00:22:27,345
[reporter 2] Sir Azeulo!

294
00:22:27,429 --> 00:22:30,057
[tense music playing]

295
00:22:30,140 --> 00:22:35,896
- [stirring music continues]
- [reporter 2] Sir Azuelo!

296
00:22:36,688 --> 00:22:39,441
[reporter 3] Sir, were you able
to capture Datu Rahman?

297
00:22:39,524 --> 00:22:41,109
[reporter 1] Sir, sir, sir!

298
00:22:41,193 --> 00:22:43,195
[reporter 4] Director Azuelo!

299
00:22:43,278 --> 00:22:45,489
[reporter 5] Sir! Sir! Sir!

300
00:22:51,703 --> 00:22:54,790
[tense music continues]

301
00:23:20,816 --> 00:23:22,984
[music intensifies]

302
00:24:02,357 --> 00:24:05,402
[Azuelo] <i>Sir, they're the members</i>
<i>of Task Force Alpha.</i>

303
00:24:05,485 --> 00:24:07,904
<i>They are in charge</i>
<i>of Datu Rahman's safety.</i>

304
00:24:07,988 --> 00:24:09,990
[Teresa] I'm just worried about Jamilah.

305
00:24:10,073 --> 00:24:11,491
[Teresa] <i>She hadn't come in</i>
<i>for a few days now.</i>

306
00:24:11,575 --> 00:24:14,161
You know how chaotic it is outside.

307
00:24:14,244 --> 00:24:16,496
[nurse] <i>Datu Rahman Abubakar</i>
<i>has gone trending.</i>

308
00:24:16,580 --> 00:24:19,040
[reporter] <i>If Datu Rahman</i>
<i>is proven innocent,</i>

309
00:24:19,124 --> 00:24:20,959
<i>he will be considered a material witness</i>

310
00:24:21,042 --> 00:24:24,629
<i>to identify the mastermind</i>
<i>behind the chaos in the country.</i>

311
00:24:24,713 --> 00:24:26,173
[glass shattering]

312
00:24:26,256 --> 00:24:27,716
[Lara] We looked
for Datu Rahman everywhere

313
00:24:27,799 --> 00:24:28,675
but we couldn't find him.

314
00:24:28,758 --> 00:24:31,219
But he surrendered to you out of the blue.

315
00:24:31,303 --> 00:24:33,889
I care for them, and they can feel that.

316
00:24:33,972 --> 00:24:35,098
You're hiding something, Espina.

317
00:24:35,182 --> 00:24:36,933
[Lara] <i>I'll find out what it is.</i>

318
00:24:37,017 --> 00:24:39,686
[Lara screams] <i>Don't touch me!</i>

319
00:24:40,562 --> 00:24:44,357
[Manuel] <i>We need to execute</i>
<i>the plan right now.</i>

320
00:24:44,441 --> 00:24:47,235
<i>Just make sure it'll reach our targets.</i>

321
00:24:47,319 --> 00:24:49,196
<i>I don't want there to be any issues.</i>
